description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you have personal lived experience of coping with wellbeing challenges both mentally and physically? Have these challenges been increased because you are from a BAME background or because you have a disability or other protected characteristic? If so, would you like to use this experience to help others?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a part time Wellbeing &amp; Lifestyle Coach who can actively support individuals to identify and work towards achieving personal goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working within a small team and focusing predominately on female staff and those from a BAME background or with disabilities or other protected characteristics that may ordinarily deter them from accessing support, the Wellbeing &amp; Lifestyle Coach will inspire hope and belief and act as a wellbeing champion - empowering our staff to achieve their hopes, dreams and goals.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Wellbeing &amp; Lifestyle Coach will receive appropriate support and training to enable them to carry out the day-to-day duties of the post and as employees of the Trust, will have full access to our staff health and wellbeing offer, including counselling and other occupational health services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IMPORTANT: &lt;/strong&gt;The role will involve regular travel across multiple sites in the North West Boroughs Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust catchment area. Therefore, the post holder must be able to meet the travel requirements of this post. Please indicate on your application how you meet this requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome applications from under-represented groups and in particular BAME applicants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Zoe Sarangi, Head of Occupational Health and Wellbeing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;zoe.sarangi@nwbh.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
